[[Category:Scots adjectives]]
#dark; soot-coloured
#:'''quotations:'''
#:*1785:"O Thou! whatever title suit thee-<br>Auld Hornie, Satan, Nick, or Clootie,<br>Wha in yon cavern grim an' '''sootie''',<br>Clos'd under hatches,<br>Spairges about the brunstane cootie,<br>To scaud poor wretches!" &mdash; ''[[s:Address to the Deil|Address to the Deil]]'' [[w:Robert Burns|Robert Burns]]
#:*"Thou ca's me Hornie, Nick an' Clootie,<br>An' tells my cave is grim an' '''sootie''';<br>But stop, thou'lt, may-be, be my booty;<br>I'll try my skill;<br>I'll gang as far as Fate will let me,<br>An' wi' guid will." &mdash; ''The Devil's Answer to the Poet's Address'' [[w:John Lapraik|John Lapraik]]